unwound.description: The most frequently referenced alignment option for a second tube is one that would serve Alameda, San Francisco‚Äôs South of Market area via Mission or Third streets, and the western districts via Geary Boulevard. Furthermore, regardless of whether economic activity increases to the degree envisioned, for the foreseeable future, transbay travel demand will continue to be primarily concentrated near the Market Street corridor. The service will include five trips both ways on Saturday and Sunday. Currently, ferry service between Richmond and San Francisco is only available on weekdays.
